<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-57-0803 </DOCNO><TEXT>A method based on the utilization of magnetic field and field gradientdistributions for calculating the gradient of the magnetic surface function,nablapsi, in stellarator systems is treated. The distributions of nablapsiand associated quantities over the magnetic surfaces of torsatrons obtainedby this method are discussed. The method can also be applied to othertoroidal systems which confine plasma in an asymmetrical magnetic field.(author). 21 refs, 4 figs, 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>